  description:
  - The liver is a vital organ located in the upper right quadrant of the abdomen,
    just below the diaphragm and to the right of the stomach. It is the largest glandular
    organ in the human body and performs many important functions that are essential
    to the body's overall health and well-being.  The liver has a unique structure
    that allows it to carry out its many functions. It is made up of thousands of
    small lobules, each of which contains liver cells called hepatocytes, as well
    as blood vessels, bile ducts, and other specialized cells.
  - 'The pleura is a thin, double-layered membrane that surrounds the lungs and lines
    the inside of the chest cavity. It consists of two layers:  Visceral pleura:
    This layer covers the lungs and is in direct contact with their surface. It is
    a thin, transparent layer of mesothelial cells that are tightly adhered to the
    lung tissue.  Parietal pleura: This layer lines the inside of the chest cavity
    and is separated from the visceral pleura by a small amount of pleural fluid.
    It is composed of two layers: the outer layer, which is attached to the chest
    wall, and the inner layer, which is in contact with the visceral pleura.'
  - The stomach is a muscular sac located in the upper abdomen, between the esophagus
    and the small intestine. It plays a vital role in the digestive system, as it
    receives food from the esophagus and mixes it with digestive juices to begin
    the process of breaking it down into nutrients that can be absorbed by the body.
  location:
  - 'The liver is located in the upper right quadrant of the abdomen, just below
    the diaphragm and to the right of the stomach. It is the largest glandular organ
    in the human body and is divided into four lobes: the right lobe, left lobe,
    caudate lobe, and quadrate lobe.'
  - The pleura is a thin, double-layered membrane that surrounds the lungs and lines
    the inside of the chest cavity. It is located in the thoracic cavity, which is
    the part of the body that lies between the neck and the abdomen.
  - 'The stomach is located in the upper abdomen, between the esophagus and the small
    intestine. It is situated in the left upper quadrant of the abdomen, just below
    the left ribcage. '
